{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"anchor":"Layouts","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Layouts"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional helper texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"inverse","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": like the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" layout but with a trailing checkbox indicator and a leading optional image","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Indicator states","anchor":"Indicator-states","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The checkbox indicator has three available states:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"selected","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": the checkbox is filled with a tick, the user has made the action to select the checkbox","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"unselected","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": the checkbox is empty, does not contain a tick, the user has made the action to unselect or did not select yet the checkbox","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"indeterminate","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": mike a prefilled or preticked checkbox, the user did not do anything on it yet","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need a checkbox with only two states to manage use instead ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Particular cases","anchor":"Particular-cases","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the ","type":"text"},{"code":"isError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag is risen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition, the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"but this component must not be considered as disabled.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The component does not follow the right-to-left (RTL) \/ left-to-right (LTR) mode returned by the system as it could have some meaning","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to have for example the indicator in trailing position for LTR mode and vice versa.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, if the component has an icon in leading position (RTL mode) or in trailing position (LTR), the content of the icon is never changed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It could lead to a loss of meaning or semantics in the icon. Thus a specific flag can be used to flip the icon content whatever the layout direction is.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It prevents the user do implement its own rules to flip or not image.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Accessibility considerations","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and helper texts and a custom checkbox trait.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Forbidden by design","anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component."}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component."}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an indeterminate state checkbox","    @Published var selection: OUDSCheckboxIndicatorState = .indeterminate","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and a description as helper text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Bazinga!\", selection: $selection, description: \"Doll-Dagga Buzz-Buzz Ziggety-Zag\")","","    \/\/ A trailing checkbox with a label, an helper text and an icon.","    \/\/ The reversed layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  description: \"Of dreaming boys and wide-eyed girls\",","                                  isReversed: true,","                                  icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  isError: true,","                                  errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                                  hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and and icon but with the icon flipped vertically","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Cocorico !\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                                  flipIcon: true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Hello world\", selection: $selection, isReadOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to manage the RTL mode quite easily and switch your layouts (flip image, indicator in RTL leading i.e. in the right):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate(\"Cocorico !\",","                                  selection: $selection,","                                  icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                                  flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft,","                                  isReversed: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"text":"Suggestions","anchor":"Suggestions","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"According to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the checkbox by default must be used in unselected state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unified-design-system.orange.com"}],"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","overridingTitle":"unified-design-system.orange.com"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Orange Compact","anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Sosh","anchor":"Sosh","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Wireframe","anchor":"Wireframe","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2.4.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Version","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.12.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Since","type":"aside","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudscheckboxitemindeterminate"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Checkbox is a UI element that allows to select multiple options from a set of mutually non exclusive choices.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Checkbox item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemInd